105
 
We should go outdoors for some contests now, All the athletic events, so that this stranger
Can tell his friends back home how good we are In boxing, wrestling, jumping, and footraces."

And with that he led them outdoors. The herald Hung the clear-toned lyre on its peg
And led Demodocus by the hand Out of the hall and along the road
The nobles had gone down to see the games. They made their way to the assembly grounds, And huge crowds trailed along, thousands Past counting.
 

110










115








